buckshee
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a trip to England or free return trip; a superficial wound meriting a return home; `a blighty'; `a homer' (prob from adj.).  to NZ
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also backsheesh
